# NOTE: Keep this list short (~8 entries). Remove old ones as new ones land.
CHANGELOG = [
    "Bump hunger decay 0.7 -> 1.0 per move to make the food clock bite (build 374). Playtest-372/373 validation showed the food clock was decorative: F1-F3 mean hunger 74.5, F4-F6 70.8, 0/18 runs ever crossed the Hungry threshold (40), 0/18 starvation deaths despite peak inventory nutrition holding at 1560 across the sweep. The 0.7/move rate dates from build 327, when the food economy was much sparser -- since then Iron Rations stack went 1->3 (b328), F1 dungeon vendors got Rations + Iron Rations (b328), and the starter pack added Cooking Kit + extra rations. With ~410 nut per vendor visit vs. ~210 at the time of the original tuning, going back to 1/move (the pre-b327 default, +43% decay rate) should restore real hunger pressure without re-introducing the F3-F4 starvation gate. Concrete impact: 60 turns from full hunger -> Hungry threshold (was 86), 90 turns -> Starving (was 129), 100 turns -> 0 (was 143). Tracker pair (HUNGER_DECAY_PER_MOVE=10 / HUNGER_DECAY_INTERVAL=10 = 1.0 flat) keeps decay integer.",
    "Curing Kit reliability: every F10+ regular vendor stocks one until purchased (build 373). Playtest-372 validation sweep (18 runs) found 2/5 F9+ first-vendor encounters skipped the kit because the vendor was a bug merchant -- the bug_merchant=True branch in Vendor.__init__ returns early before reaching the Curing Kit gate. Rather than duplicate the gate in the bug-merchant branch, switched to the cleaner 'every F10+ regular vendor stocks one until the player buys it' pattern: the gs.curing_kit_stocked one-shot flag now flips in the buy handler (vendor.py:process_vendor_action) on actual purchase, NOT on stocking. Effect: a player who walks past or only sees bug-merchant F10 vendors will still find the kit at the next F10+ regular vendor. Also bumped the floor gate F9 -> F10 (z >= 9): 78% of bug levels still spawn at F8-F10 (probability table: F8 40%, F9 24%, F10 14.4%, ...) so F10 stays the natural mid-game milestone, and in playtest mode where bug-level is always F8 the kit lands cleanly post-bug.",
    "Food-economy tuning round 1: CookingKit out of starter, CuringKit to F9+ (build 372). Playtest-371 audit (8 runs, 12977 turns) found the food clock was decorative -- mean hunger 67-77 across all runs, 0/8 ever crossed the Hungry threshold, peak inventory nutrition 2840 vs. max-hunger 100. Two culprits: (1) Cooking Kit was in the starting shop AND in the playtest starter pack, so the auto-cook policy fired from turn 1 -- zero rot events, zero raw-meat-eat decisions, cooking was a reflex button. Removed from BOTH vendor.py:starting and playtest_harness.py:starter -- kit is now F3+ vendor only, per its level=3 metadata. (2) Curing Kit was only in items.py:generate_vendor_inventory (the restock path), never in vendor.py:Vendor.__init__ (the main path) -- 0/8 runs ever saw one, the entire Bratwurst/Andouille/Boerewors sausage subsystem was dead code. Now: first vendor at F9+ (after the bug level at F8) guaranteed-stocks the Curing Kit, and the playtest harness smart-policy has an explicit 'buy curing_kit on sight' rule (right after cooking_kit, before rations). Also retired the curing_kit_floor random-roll state variable -- no longer needed with the deterministic F9+ gate.",
    "Audit + fix 5 more stack-wipe sites (build 371). After b370's two stack-wipe game bugs (Food + LanternFuel), audited every `inventory.remove(item)` / `inventory.remove_item(name)` call in the codebase. Found 5 more sites doing the same thing: (1) characters.py:burn_inventory_items wiped entire Potion/Scroll stacks on fire damage (a Fire Imp could erase 5 Healing Potions in one hit). (2) characters.py:freeze_inventory_items same for freeze (Mind Flayer ice attack erased entire potion stack). (3) items.py:Scroll-Upgrade consume wiped the entire Upgrade Scroll stack when using one. (4) combat.py:foresight-scroll consume wiped the entire Foresight Scroll stack. (5) room_actions.py:alchemist brew wiped both selected potion stacks (picking 2 Healing Potions out of an 8-Healing Potion stack consumed all 8). Plus an altar-sacrifice fix (room_actions.py:677) where sacrificing one of N stacked items destroyed the rest. All five now check item.count: decrement when >1, remove the entry only when count drops to 0. Smoke test: dwarf seed 4 (Bombur) went from b370 F11 T3530 dead -> b371 **F13 T4000 alive** at turn cap, hp 188/208. The audit caught the silent resource bleed that the warp roulette had been hiding for builds.",
    "Two stack-wipe bugs in Food / LanternFuel handling (build 370). User flagged Bombur Ironbeard (dwarf seed 4) as 'didn't eat any rations' -- traced to T161 Spore Puff combat where the agent's 8 Rations vanished in a single spore attack. The mushroom monster's rot_food_items() picks `magnitude` distinct Food entries and called `inventory.remove(item)` on each, wiping the entire stack regardless of count (8 Rations -> 0 in one hit, 400 nutrition gone). Then Luthien the Singer (elf seed 1) flagged as 'starved in a loop' -- traced to T595 where her lantern auto-refuel kicked in and called `inventory.remove_item('Lantern Fuel')` to consume a canister, wiping her entire 8-canister stack in one shot. She stranded on F5 in the dark by T717 and oscillated until T2112 starvation. Same pattern in TWO different code paths (characters.py:715 rot_food_items, items.py:2731 Lantern.use, room_actions.py:3722 auto-refuel) -- all now decrement count and only remove the entry when count drops to 0. Lantern auto-refuel also corrected from 10 -> canister's actual fuel_restore_amount (20). Smoke test: same dwarf seed 4: b369 died T819 F1 starvation, b370 reached F11 T3530 in combat (max HP 64 -> 190). The fix cascade-unlocks survival depth that the warp roulette had been masking.",
    "Don't step on warp tiles (build 369). User directive: 'why would a player step into a warp room?' Three smart-policy paths still committed agents to known W tiles. (1) `trapped_no_d -> tiers=[W, V]` (line 3488) actively targeted W as an escape. (2) `not trapped_no_d` carve-out at line 3104 dropped W from AVOID. (3) perm_wedge override of d_avoid_reachable=False (line 2995) made trapped_no_d fire even when D was genuinely reachable. dwarf seed 1 T201 had D reachable at path_dist=18, but all 3 combined fired -- W south at dist 1, adjacent-shortcut stepped onto it, warp roulette. Removed all three: W always in AVOID, trapped_no_d targets only V, no perm_wedge override of d_reach. Also softened cornered detector (line 2018) -- single fog-blind stairs_up arrival no longer marks PERMANENT (only +1, accumulates over 3 real bounces) -- and added lantern-fire FIRST in stairs_up_mode + stairs_down_mode (mirroring the game_loop gate at line 2927) so agents on corner U/D tiles with fog cardinals reveal before deciding to ascend/step-off. 9-run smoke: warps 32 -> 3, W steps 35 -> 4, avg_maxF 4.4 -> 4.6 (matches the b369 warp-roulette depth WITHOUT the warp roulette). human_5 reached F9.",
    "Stop stepping into fog (build 368). Per user directive: 'playtesters should be shining the lantern and almost never stepping into an unknown fog room'. Three smart-policy bugs were letting agents commit to fog tiles. (1) `_walkable(d)` in the random fallback (line 3889) treated `None` (fog) as walkable -- only walls and AVOID were filtered. (2) The same fallback at line 3920 ACTIVELY PREFERRED fog neighbours (`undiscovered_nbrs = ...`), inverting the user's intent. (3) `_swap_if_backtrack` (line 3759) could rewrite a known-good 's' into a fog 'w' when 's' was in recent_steps, because the alt-search filtered only AVOID and walls, not None. Fix: all three paths now treat fog as non-walkable. The lantern fire above (line 2927: fuel > 0 + any fog neighbour) handles reveal. Cornered last-resort still permits a fog step ONLY when every cardinal is wall or AVOID -- standing still to starve is worse than a coin-flip. 9-run smoke (3 races x seeds 1/5/7 x 4000T): 262 fog steps -> 2 (-99%), warps 46 -> 32 (-30%), stair-share 48% -> 56%.",
    "Shrink auto-unequips normal-size gear (build 360). User-reported bug: Bombur Axebreaker (s=10 dwarf) wound up with Adamantine Armor + Scorpion Tail Whip co-equipped -- normal-size armor and bug-size weapon at the same time. Root cause: the equip gate at game_systems.py:2263 only blocks NEW equips of the wrong size, not gear that was already equipped before the size change. _restore_size_on_bug_exit already drops bug gear when growing back, but the SHRINK direction had no symmetric unequip -- so a player descending into a bug floor in full Adamantine kit kept the armor through the shrink, then swapped the weapon slot to a bug weapon and ended up in a mixed state. Fix: _trigger_shrinking_spell now unequips any non-bug Weapon/Armor at the moment of shrinking, with flavor logs ('suddenly enormous in your tiny hands', 'slides off your shrunken frame'). Items stay in inventory so they auto-re-equip on grow-back.",
]
